features: Give a movie fan or any kid who lives for high-flying adventures a gift full of details to inspire the imagination with this LEGO Disney and Pixar ‘Up’ House (43217) set

The set includes beloved Disney and Pixar movie characters: Carl Fredricksen and Russell LEGO minifigures, and a Dug LEGO dog figure for dog lovers. The set is made for unlimited adventures on land or floating through the clouds
Disney and Pixar fans with a passion for adventure will enjoy this set full of imaginative possibilities, with a house based on an iconic movie.
One of a limited number of LEGO sets created to celebrate Disney’s 100th anniversary; collect them all! Great for kids ages 9+. This also makes an impressive gift for adult Disney fans
The LEGO Builder app guides kids on an intuitive building adventure. They can save sets, track progress and zoom in and rotate models in 3D while they build

body.description: Adventure awaits Disney fans ages 9 and up with this fun LEGO Disney and Pixar ‘Up’ House (43217). The set that everyone will be talking about includes a detailed section of the iconic house with a chimney and balloons, 2 LEGO minifigures, a LEGO dog figure, a wilderness explorer backpack and an adventure book. Kids can also enjoy an easy and intuitive building adventure with the LEGO Builder app, which lets them zoom in and rotate models in 3D, save sets and track their progress. Based on the Disney and Pixar movie Up, this set will appeal to movie fans and older kids with its many details and challenging build. Designed for play and display, it inspires imaginative adventures and can take pride of place on a shelf once play is done. This set comes with 2 LEGO minifigures, Carl Fredricksen and Russell, plus a Dug LEGO dog figure. This premium building toy makes a fun gift for adult fans of Up or older kids who want to join the hottest trend. With the house measuring over 10.5 in. (27 cm) high, 6 in. (15 cm) wide and 4 in. (11 cm) deep, this set is made for endless play sessions or display in kids’ (or adults’) rooms

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A High-Flying Adventure in a Box
reviews.reviewText: A LEGO enthusiast and a massive fan of Disney and Pixar's 'Up', I was thrilled to embark on the adventure that is the 'Up' House by LEGO, set 43217. This set is more than just a collection of bricks; it's a journey into a world of imagination, creativity, and fun.The first thing that struck me about this set was its affordability. For only $60, and with 598 pieces, it offers a substantial and satisfying building experience without breaking the bank. It's a testament to LEGO's commitment to making quality and enjoyable building sets accessible to all.The build itself was a joy from start to finish. The instructions were clear and easy to follow, making the process smooth and enjoyable. I appreciated the intuitive building adventure offered by the LEGO Builder app, which allowed me to zoom in and rotate models in 3D, save sets, and track my progress. It added an extra layer of interactivity to the building experience, making it even more engaging.Building the 'Up' House was not just fun; it was also surprisingly easy. Despite its detailed design and numerous pieces, the set was designed with simplicity in mind. It's suitable for Disney fansaged 9 and up, making it a great introduction to the world of LEGO for younger builders. But don't let its simplicity fool you; this set offers a challenging and rewarding build that will appeal to older kids and adults alike.Once completed, the 'Up' House is a sight to behold. The set captures the charm and whimsy of the iconic house from the movie, complete with a chimney and balloons. It's a colorful and vibrant display piece that will brighten up any room. The set also includes a detailed section of the house with different rooms and functions, adding an extra layer of playability to the set.The set also includes two LEGO minifigures, Carl Fredricksen and Russell, plus a Dug LEGO dog figure. These beloved characters bring the set to life and inspire endless imaginative adventures. Whether you're recreating scenes from the movie or embarking on new adventures, these figures add a touch of magic to the set.The 'Up' House is a high-flying adventure in a box. It offers an affordable, fun, and easy build that results in a stunning display piece. Whether you're a fan of 'Up', a LEGO enthusiast, or simply someone who enjoys a good build, this set is a must-have. So grab your wilderness explorer backpack, open your adventure book, and get ready to embark on a building journey like no other with the 'Up' House by LEGO. Adventure is out there!
